<p id="Par122" class="p">This time-varying budget equation can be used to derive a modified expression for ∆
 <italic class="italic">T</italic> (in a similar manner to that used to derive Eq. 
 <xref rid="Equ19" ref-type="" class="xref">M11</xref>):
 <disp-formula id="Equ26" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">M18</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M53" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\Delta T = - (\Delta F_{\mathrm{A}} + \Delta C_{\mathrm{O}} + R_{\mathrm{F}} + R_{\mathrm{C}}-{\mathrm{d}}H/{\mathrm{d}}t + {\mathrm{d}}H_{{\mathrm{OBS}}}/{\mathrm{d}}t)/(\lambda _{\mathrm{F}} + \lambda _{\mathrm{C}})$$\end{document}</tex-math>
